Occupants
of a grey Jaguar XJ were robbed of an undisclosed amount of money at the corner of
Main Reef Road and Hanover Street near Crown Mines. According
to the police, the armed men stopped the Jaguar and ordered the occupants to
get out of the car. In
the video, the armed men can be seen taking out items form the Jaguar in to the
white Ford Ranger. As
they were still busy with the robbery, gunshots could be heard and the thugs can
be seem running for dear life. While
they were trying to escape from the scene, one of the thugs could be seen
hanging on to the back speeding off bakkie. According to cops a case of armed robbery and attempted has been opened. 